<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
2 MEN ARRESTED IN DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men have been charged with attempted murder in a gang-related shooting in 
December, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A dispute between two rival Filipino gangs led to the drive-by shooting at 3813 
Merrill Court the night of Dec. 23, said Simi Valley Police Sgt. Arch Morgan. 
</P>
<P>
The bullets narrowly missed three residents inside the house. No one was 
injured. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested were Clint Gellekanao, 22, of Pico Rivera and Franley Jardeleza, 27, 
of Pacoima. 
</P>
<P>
Handguns were seized in both homes, including a 9-millimeter handgun believed 
to be related to the shooting, Morgan said. 
</P>
<P>
Both men were booked Wednesday on charges of attempted murder and shooting at 
an occupied dwelling, Morgan said. CAROL WATSON 
</P>
