<P>
CITY OPENS 24-HOUR INFORMATION LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city of Stanton has opened a telephone information line that gives 
residents a recorded schedule of events sponsored by the city. 
</P>
<P>
The line, which was installed last month, provides a three-minute recorded 
message containing City Council meeting schedules, the mayor's office hours, 
information on special-interest classes, such as courses on income tax 
preparation, and numbers for city offices. 
</P>
<P>
The message is updated every month. 
</P>
<P>
"We wanted to develop a device through which we could provide information to 
the community," said Terry Matz, the city manager. "We're providing a summary 
of information that we think people will need." 
</P>
<P>
Matz said members of the council last year suggested the city open an 
information line to keep residents better posted on upcoming events. He added: 
"This is a 24-hour service. We hope people will take advantage of it." 
</P>
<P>
The Information Line number is (714) 220-0500. 
</P>
</TEXT>
