<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN COURT: A SUMMARY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA-RELATED BUSINESS LITIGATION 
DEVELOPMENTS DURING THE PAST WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAARP Sues Commissioner: The California Automobile Assigned Risk Plan filed 
suit against state Insurance Commissioner Roxani M. Gillespie on Tuesday in Los 
Angeles Superior Court seeking a court order overturning Gillespie's December, 
1989, denial of a rate increase for the plan, which provides the minimum auto 
liability coverage to drivers who are unable to purchase it in the private 
sector. CAARP appealed Gillespie's 1989 decision to the California Supreme 
Court, which declined to hear the case. (Filed March 20 1990; Case No. C755745) 
</P>
</TEXT>
