MORNING REPORT: MOVIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cinema Editor Awards: In the last of the guild awards preceding the Oscars 
themselves, the Eddie, presented by the American Cinema Editors, went to Steven 
Rosenblum for his work on "Glory." 
</P>
<P>
Byron Brandt was honored for his editing of the television special "Howard 
Beach: Making the Case for Murder." Paul Zinner and John Burnett won for their 
editing of an episode of "War and Remembrance." "Roger &amp; Me," the 
controversial documentary about General Motors and Flint, Mich., earned Eddies 
for two first-time editors, Wendey Stanzler (who is from Flint) and Jennifer 
Beman. During Sunday night ceremonies in Beverly Hills, a special ACE award 
went to Steven Spielberg as filmmaker of the decade. CLAUDIA PUIG 
