<P>
IVANA SEEKS HALF TRUMP FORTUNE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ivana Trump asked a court today to declare that she is entitled to half of her 
husband Donald's estimated $5-billion fortune, but her lawyers said she is not 
seeking a divorce. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Kennedy, Ivana Trump's attorney, told a news conference, "This is not 
an action for either divorce or separation. Mrs. Trump remains committed to her 
marriage and her family. 
</P>
<P>
This is an action to obtain rights to half the fortune which the Trumps built 
together during the course of their 13-year-marriage." 
</P>
<P>
A 24-page complaint was filed with New York State Supreme Court against Donald 
Trump, the real estate magnate whose marital problems have been the talk of New 
York for the past month. He has allegedly been linked with an actress named 
Marla Maples but has not sought a divorce or separation from his wife. 
</P>
</TEXT>
