<P>
YORBA LINDA SYNAGOGUE, CHURCH DENOUNCE ANTI-SEMITIC FLYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
YORBA LINDA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities today are seeking the identity of those responsible for 
distributing hundreds of anti-Semitic flyers with a "Kill Every Jew" message 
found near a Yorba Linda synagogue and a Protestant church over the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
The flyers were found Sunday morning littering the neighborhood surrounding the 
Chabad Center of North County, an ultra-Orthodox synagogue, and the Yorba Linda 
United Methodist Church. 
</P>
<P>
Police and church officials said this morning the flyers were "falsely and 
fraudulently" attributed to the "Methodist fellowship." 
</P>
<P>
"They were probably seeking credibility," said Brea police Lt. Tom Christian. 
"They were probably trying to give somebody reason to think that they should 
read it." 
</P>
<P>
Church and synagogue officials condemned the flyers after a meeting today at 
the Chabad Center. "This is a non-event," said Rabbi David Eliezrie. "One 
person must have photocopied a piece of paper. . . . It is not a problem for 
ourselves or our sister community." 
</P>
<P>
The Rev. Kenneth Criswell, pastor at the United Methodist Church, called the 
flyers "terrible and cruel." 
</P>
</TEXT>
