<P>
TEXANS WALK TALL ON TV SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN ANTONIO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Mayor Henry Cisneros will be host of a new syndicated series of TV 
specials featuring interviews with Texas celebrities. 
</P>
<P>
"Texans," scheduled to debut in April, will be shown in Texas, New Mexico and 
Oklahoma. 
</P>
<P>
The first show will feature former Dallas Cowboys Coach Tom Landry, 
country-Western singer Janie Fricke and Dr. Red Duke, a trauma surgeon in 
Houston, executive producer Bob Phillips said. 
</P>
