<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
WINFIELD DENIES TRADE RUMOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FT. LAUDERDALE, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York Yankee outfielder Dave Winfield, who missed all of last season because 
of back surgery, fielded questions Sunday about reports that he may be traded 
to the Angels for pitcher Mike Witt. 
</P>
<P>
The Yankees have had talks with the Angels about Witt, 9-15 with a 4.54 ERA 
last season, but they deny Winfield is involved. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't know anything about that," principal owner George Steinbrenner said. 
</P>
<P>
"They can't just trade me," Winfield said. "I have rights, and no one has said 
anything to me." As a player with 10 or more years in the majors and five or 
more with the same club, Winfield may veto any trade. His home is in Beverly 
Hills, so there is speculation that Winfield might accept a trade to 
California. 
</P>
<P>
"I won't comment because people will read too much into it," he said. "Any 
decisions have to come between George and me. Other than Jackie Robinson, I 
don't know a player who has been badgered more than me. I'm not going to let 
anything distract me from my comeback trail." 
</P>
</TEXT>
